    <h3 class="vspace">
        <strong>College Board Contractor Guidelines</strong>
    </h3>
    <p class="vspace">
        <em>The following Guidelines must be signed and returned to your vendor prior to starting work at the College Board.</em>
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        <strong>Our Mission:</strong>
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        The College Board’s mission is to connect students to college success and opportunity. We are a not-for-profit membership organization committed to excellence and equality in education. Information about the College Board’s products and services may be found on our website, <a href="www.collegeboard.org" target="_blank">www.collegeboard.org</a>.
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        <strong>Time Reporting:</strong>
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        Please support the College Board by providing accurate time reporting in our tracking system. The time you enter into the College Board’s System is considered your master time record, for work conducted under contract with The College Board, and should match the time you enter into your company’s time reporting system to avoid any delays in invoice processing. Fraudulent time reporting is taken very seriously and could lead to invoice non-payment and/or cause for dismissal.
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        Please refer to the Planview “Entering Time” tear sheet enclosed in this packet for instructions on how to enter your time and work with your CB manager for time entry questions.
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        <strong>Planned and Unplanned Leave:</strong>
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        Please do not charge time for personal activities that occur during the work day. You are expected to only charge your actual working time even if that is short of a 40 hour work week. The College Board has a standard 40 hour work week. Unpaid leave or attendance requests must be discussed in advance with your CB manager and the request submitted, in writing, for approval.
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        If you are unable to come into the office, you are required to let your CB manager know at the beginning of that day via phone or email.
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        <strong>Over Time:</strong>
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        At times, your project may require additional effort beyond 40 hours. In order for your CB manager to maintain an accurate budget we ask that you receive written permission in advance (estimated hours of OT) with your CB manager for any over time you need to work to complete your assignment.
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        <strong>Contract Terms:</strong>
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        The College Board would like as much notice as possible if you are not able to work through the terms of your contract. Please provide notice/resignation information to your vendor with as much advance notice as possible. Common professional business practice is to offer two full weeks notice to your employer prior to leaving the organization. Of course, we would appreciate additional notice if that is available.
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        At the end of your assignment please ensure your building access key and badge are returned to your CB manager, or to the main receptionist and make your manager aware of any College Board equipment that you may have been using.
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        <strong>Security Awareness Training:</strong>
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        Contractors are required to take College Board’s mandatory security awareness training. You will receive an email invitation shortly after your start date. If you do not receive this email, please contact <a href="mailto:securityawareness@collegeboard.org">securityawareness@collegeboard.org</a> to request this training.
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        <strong>Communications:</strong>
    </p>
    <p class="vspace">
        As our most frequent mode of communication, e-mail must be composed with the seriousness of any business correspondence.
    </p>
